%N A397159 Decimal expansion of the midradius of a canonical (dual-uniform) tetragonal trapezohedron with unit short edge length.
%C A397159 The tetragonal trapezohedron is the dual polyhedron of the square antiprism.
%H A397159 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A397159/b397159.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A397159 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/TetragonalTrapezohedron.html">Tetragonal Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397159 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Square_antitegum">Square antitegum</a>.
%H A397159 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Trapezohedron.html">Trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397159 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tetragonal_trapezohedron">Tetragonal trapezohedron</a>.
%H A397159 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_04">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 4</a>.
%F A397159 Equals sqrt(1/2 + 3/(4*sqrt(2))) = sqrt(1/2 + 3/A010487).
%F A397159 Equals the largest real root of 32*x^4 - 32*x^2 - 1.
%e A397159 1.0150517651282178048743127233968454051665031774103...
%t A397159 First[RealDigits[Sqrt[1/2 + 3/Sqrt[32]], 10, 100]]
%t A397159 (* Alternative: *)
%t A397159 First[RealDigits[PolyhedronData[{"Trapezohedron", 4}, "Midradius"], 10, 100]]
